General Motors Corp's Chevrolet andOldsmobile divisions said they are extending cash rebates anddiscount financing on several car and truck lines through thesummer.    Chevrolet said that through August 3 its customers couldchoose cash rebates of 300 dlrs to 1,000 dlrs depending onmodels or loan rates beginning at 3.9 pct through 9.9 pct,depending on length of contract. The program covers six carlines and S-10 Blazer and pickup trucks.    Oldsmobile said separately its cash rebates and discountfinancing packages with rates beginning at 3.9 pct for 24-monthloans were continued retroactively to June 16 on its Delta 88and 98 Regency models.    It gave no expiration for its incentive program.    Chevrolet said its program continues to cover its newlyintroduced Corsica and Beretta compact cars.    Through June 10, Chevrolet's car sales are 14.1 pct belowlast year's levels while Oldsmobile's retail deliveries of carsare off by 31.9 pct. Reuter&#3;